  "fun_fact": "Sorbitan monopalmitate (Span 40) is the 'Goldilocks' of the sorbitan family - not too water-loving like Span 20, not too oil-loving like Span 60, but just right for many food applications. It's named after palmitic acid, which was first isolated from palm oil!"
